ref: Jour: Physical Review, Part C, Nuclear Physics, Vol.20, p.1517 (1979)
title: Production of Argon Isotopes By Spallation of Sc,Ti, Fe,Co,Ni and Cu.

x4freetext: PRODUCTION OF ARGON ISOTOPES BY SPALLATION OF SC,TI,
FE,CO,NI AND CU.

x4codes.hlp: Centre d`Etudes Nucleaires de Bordeaux-Gradignan, France

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Physical Review, Part C, Nuclear Physics, Vol.20, p.1517 (1979)

x4freetext: THE TARGETS CONSISTED OF STACKS OF 20*20 MM SQUARES OF
METAL FOIL OF THICKNESS 0.010 TO 0.050 MM.AL FOIL WAS
INSERTED BETWEEN THE TARGET FOILS (SC,TI,V,FE,CO,NI
AND CU) TO SERVE AS QUARDS,RECOIL COLLECTORS AND
MONITORS.THE THICKNESSES OF THE STACKS WERE 0.15 G/
CM**2 FOR THE IRRADIATION AT 0.080 GEV,0.3 TO 0.5 G/
CM**2 AT 0.15,0.6,AND 24 GEV,AND 1.5 G/CM**2 AT 1.05
GEV.EACH TARGET CONTAINED EITHER 3 TO 6 MONITORS.
.SEMIEMPIRICAL FITS.

x4codes.shortRef: Rept: Centre d`Etudes Nucleaires, note, No.1466 (1971)

x4freetext: THE ARGON SAMPLES WERE ANALYZED IN A 60 DEGREE
SECTOR,12 CM RADIUS MASS SPECTROMETER (A MODIFIED
MICROMASS-12).
.THE IRRADIATED WERE CARRIED OUT IN THE FOLLOWING
ACCELERATORS-LOUVAIN-LA-NEUVE (0.080GEV),SATURNE (1.05
GEV),ORSAY (0.150 GEV) AND CERN (0.6 AND 24 GEV).

x4codes.hlp: Off-line mass separation of a product

x4freetext: .AT 0.6 AND 24 GEV.TO TEST THE INFLUENCE OF BEAM
INTENSITY.
THE ROOT MEAN SQUARE OF THE VARIOUS ERRORS IS
CALCULATED FOR EACH MEASUREMENT,I.E.,TARGET PREPARATION
(THICKNESS,0.5 TO 3%,IMPURITIES,0 TO 1%),MONITORING
AND ALIGNMENT (3 TO 7%),BLANKS FOR APPARATUS AND METALS
(IN MOST CASES,O TO 1%,SOMETIMES 1 TO 80%),ZERO-TIME
CORRECTIONS TO MASS-SPECTROMETER ANALYSIS (0 TO 1%,
SOMETIMES 1 TO 5%),RE-EXTRACTIONS (0 TO 1%) AND
CALIBRATION (7 TO 12%).FOR ISOTOPE RATIOS THE MOST
IMPORTANT ERRORS CANCEL OUT,BUT AN ERROR OF 2% IS
ADDED TO ACCOUNT FOR A POSSIBLE SYSTEMATIC INSTRUMENTAL
ERROR.
1.THE UNCERTAINTY IN THE CROSS SECTION MEASUREMENTS
IS FROM 10 TO 20 PER CENT.
2.THE UNCERTAINTY IN THE RATIOS IS FROM 2 TO 5 PER
CENT.
.SEE 1.
.SEE 2.

x4code.headerHelp: Error in value of quantity, defined under ERR-ANALYS

x4freetext: .THE UNCERTAINTY IS REPORTED BY AUTHORS.
/BY AUTHORS/.IN GENERAL,EACH TARGET ELEMENT WAS
SUBJECTED TO THREE INDEPENDENT IRRADIATIONS AT EACH
ENERGY E(P) AND TWO YEARS,AT LEAST,ELAPSED BETWEEN
IRRADIATION ANA ANALYSIS.
